If you get an "reload_m not found" error when trying to run some
of the Statex options under the Statex mainmenu, you need to
update your "menus.frm" file with the following code:

..
.expr reload_m \
    Menu_Zap(nil),
    PRINTF( "^[]Z^[\\" )
.expr reload_menus \
    Menu_Zap(nil),
    PRINTF( "^[]Z^[\\" ),
    DIAG( "All mouse menus have been reloaded with new values." )
.export reload_menus,reload_m
..
 
